content: प्रसह् {c1c} <ab>A.</ab> {@--1@} To bear, endure; न तेजस्तेजस्वी प्रसृतमपरेषां प्रसहते <ls>U. 6. 14.</ls> {@--2@} To withstand, resist, overpower; संयुगे सायुगीनं तमुद्यतं प्रसहेत कः <ls>Ku. 2. 57.</ls> {@--3@} To exert oneself, attempt. {@--4@} To dare, venture, be able. {@--5@} To have power or energy; see प्रसह्य.
प्रस(सा)ह् {%<ab>m.</ab>%} <ab>Ved.</ab> {@--1@} Force, violence. {@--2@} An epithet of Indra.
